      "author": "jaliriogbarrios19",
      "description": "## v0.4.0 — Bahá'í Faith Research Domain\n\n### New Domain: Fe Bahá'í\n\nSelect \"Fe Bahá'í\" from the domain dropdown to generate doctrinal research briefs based on the Bahá'í Sacred Writings and official sources.\n\n**How it works:**\n- The LLM draws from its training knowledge of Bahá'í texts (Bahá'u'lláh, 'Abdu'l-Bahá, Shoghi Effendi, Universal House of Justice, the Báb)\n- No PubMed/OpenAlex search — direct LLM-based generation\n- Lightweight citation verification against known Bahá'í text titles\n- Direct deep links to specific texts on reference.bahai.org\n- Original Spanish titles + English equivalents in all references\n\n**Brief structure:**\n- Research Question\n- Findings per Source (thematic H4 subtitles, ~150 words each, inline citations, direct quotes from Writings)\n- Synthesis & Implications (3-4 paragraphs)\n\n**Official sources:**\n- reference.bahai.org (Bahá'í Reference Library — canonical texts)\n- bahai.org (Bahá'í International Community — official statements)\n- news.bahai.org (Bahá'í World News Service)\n\n### Refactor\n\nSplit research-engine.ts (693 lines) and research-modal.ts (472 lines) into 10 focused modules. All 13 source files now under 300 lines.\n\n### Verification\n\nQuotes generated by the LLM come from training data, not live text access. A disclaimer is included recommending verification against reference.bahai.org before academic use.\n",
